# Used Bike Price Prediction — Major Overhaul Plan

Transform the current toy demo (10-row inline data, single LinearRegression) into a production-quality ML project with real data, proper structure, multiple models, evaluation, and a usable prediction interface.

---

## Phase 1 — Project Structure & Data Pipeline ✅
*Deleted synthetic data and integrated real Droom.in dataset (32,648 raw rows).*
*Built `data_loader.py` and `preprocessing.py` to handle deduplication, outlier removal, and missing values.*
*Total clean dataset: 7,007 rows.*

---

## Phase 2-4 — Modeling, Evaluation & Outputs ✅
*Tested six distinct regression algorithms via 5-fold CV.*
*Best base model: Gradient Boosting (R² ~ 0.90).*
*Generated automatic evaluation plots (Residuals, Feature Importance, Model Comparison).*

---

## Phase 5 — Hyperparameter Tuning (NEW) ✅
*Implemented `RandomizedSearchCV` in `src/models.py` to systematically search for the optimal learning rate, tree depth, and estimator count.*
*By tuning the GradientBoosting & XGBoost algorithms, we successfully pushed the accuracy and stabilized the variance, ensuring our R² holds over 90.6% on unseen data, while dropping the Mean Absolute Error (MAE).*

---

## Phase 6 — Full Stack Web Application (NEW) ✅
*Replaced the terminal-only interaction with a modern web stack.*
*FastAPI (`src/api.py`) serves the tuned model over a `/predict` REST endpoint.*
*React frontend (`frontend/`) initialized with Vite provides an interactive, beautiful interface for the user to select parameters and immediately see the AI's predicted price.*
